<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🐼 M003 Extension — Build the Panda (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> 3D Panda (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner (Extension, after Week 6) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>Build a standing panda in 3D — <strong>white body</strong>, <strong>black ears</strong>, <strong>black eyes</strong>, <strong>black legs</strong>. Every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>: x <strong>across</strong>, y <strong>up</strong>, z <strong>deeper</strong> (forward).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move, and the panda moves too.</p>
<p>🎨 White parts = <strong>white concrete</strong>. Black parts = <strong>black wool</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the code. Circle one word.</p>
<pre><code>place black block at (2, 5, 1)
place black block at (2, 6, 1)
place black block at (2, 7, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only y changes. This is a leg climbing... Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<pre><code>place white block at (2, 8, 1)
place white block at (2, 8, 2)
place white block at (2, 8, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only z changes. Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>An ear sits <strong>on top</strong> of the head, one step up, at (2, 9, 1). The code below has only <strong>two</strong> numbers, so it lands flat on the ground.</p>
<pre><code># broken
place black block at (2, 9)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fill the blank to fix it:</strong></p>
<pre><code>place black block at (2, 9, __)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Which number fills the blank? Circle one:</strong> 1 · 3</p>
<p><strong>What was missing? Circle one:</strong> the z number · the color</p>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Look at the 🐼 panda in the world. Walk around it. See the ears up top, the eye patches, and the two legs at the bottom.</p>
<p><strong>Build a small panda on your home spot.</strong> Keep it easy:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>White head: fill white blocks from (2, 5, 1) up to (5, 8, 1) — a small square.</p>
<p>Two black ears on top: black block at (2, 9, 1) and (5, 9, 1).</p>
<p>Two black eyes on the front: black block at (2, 7, 1) and (5, 7, 1).</p>
<p>Two black legs at the bottom: black block at (2, 4, 1) and (5, 4, 1).</p>
<p>💡 Tip: ears go <strong>up</strong> (bigger y). Legs go <strong>down</strong> (smaller y). Eyes only show on the <strong>front</strong> (z = 1).</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> — one take, no stopping (a phone is fine). Show these in order:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera at the panda. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Say these out loud, filling in the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
<p>The most fun part was ______.</p>
<p>Something new I learned was ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your <strong>one</strong> video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
